"2048451460413673678", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZaQK8v9", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 27, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8583117, "raw_content": "", "author": "PatriotSam", "created": 1777227463012, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Han_Schlomo", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZaQK8v9.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/ChrisWillx/status/2048451460413673678?s=20", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "How in the hell do 72% of men have a positive view of women?", "last_comment_created": 1777235235429, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 15, "score_up": 27, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 68, "created": 1777223861000, "id": "2048451460413673678", "video": false, "poll": false, "user": {"profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1612136768194625536/7HdwNsOD_normal.jpg", "displayName": "Chris Williamson", "username": "ChrisWillx"}, "content": "Women feel much more negatively towards young men than young men feel about them.\n\n72% of men have a positive view of women.\n\n50% of women have a neutral or negative view of men.\n\n21% of women have an actively negative view of men.\n\nOnly 7% of men feel the same.\n\nFor all the talk", "parentTweet": false, "likes": 500}}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "text", "uuid": "1ASZaQK93L", "is_twitter": false, "is_admin": false, "score": 25, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8583133, "raw_content": "The media frames the car bomb at Dunmurry mainly through the old Northern Ireland lens: the New IRA, police as a target, and the legacy of The Troubles. That is not wrong.\n\nBut the question is whether this misses the newer context. What if old rivals join hands?\n\nAcross the island of Ireland, an anti-migration and anti-asylum movement is also growing, with old rivals \u2014 Irish nationalists and Northern Irish loyalists \u2014 partly beginning to find common ground. If migration becomes a bridge issue between groups that historically opposed each other, this is not just \u201cunrest\u201d; it becomes a new security risk for Ireland, Northern Ireland, the UK and the EU.\n\nQuestion for the media: is this attack being interpreted only as a remnant of the past, or also as a signal within a newly explosive field of migration frustration, old paramilitary structures and cross-border radicalisation? If old rivals join hands.. we have a situation...\n\nSource on the car bomb: The Guardian reports that police suspect the New IRA. \n\nhttps://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2026/apr/26/car-explosion-dunmurry-police-station-belfast-northern-ireland\n\nSource on the new anti-migration dynamic: The Irish Times previously reported that anti-migration figures in the Republic are cooperating with loyalist groups in Northern Ireland. \n\nhttps://www.irishtimes.com/crime-law/2025/07/09/far-right-groups-co-operating-across-border-as-shared-grievances-override-sectarian-fault-lines/", "author": "MulderNetherlands", "created": 1777228108349, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "BOHICA2021", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "", "removal_source": "", "link": "", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "Car bomb in Ireland goes off: media forgets to mention resent uprising ", "last_comment_created": 1777235771432, "content": "<p>The media frames the car bomb at Dunmurry mainly through the old Northern Ireland lens: the New IRA, police as a target, and the legacy of The Troubles. That is not wrong.</p>\n<p>But the question is whether this misses the newer context. What if old rivals join hands?</p>\n<p>Across the island of Ireland, an anti-migration and anti-asylum movement is also growing, with old rivals \u2014 Irish nationalists and Northern Irish loyalists \u2014 partly beginning to find common ground. If migration becomes a bridge issue between groups that historically opposed each other, this is not just \u201cunrest\u201d; it becomes a new security risk for Ireland, Northern Ireland, the UK and the EU.</p>\n<p>Question for the media: is this attack being interpreted only as a remnant of the past, or also as a signal within a newly explosive field of migration frustration, old paramilitary structures and cross-border radicalisation? If old rivals join hands.. we have a situation...</p>\n<p>Source on the car bomb: The Guardian reports that police suspect the New IRA.</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2026/apr/26/car-explosion-dunmurry-police-station-belfast-northern-ireland\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2026/apr/26/car-explosion-dunmurry-police-station-belfast-northern-ireland</a></p>\n<p>Source on the new anti-migration dynamic: The Irish Times previously reported that anti-migration figures in the Republic are cooperating with loyalist groups in Northern Ireland.</p>\n<p><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.irishtimes.com/crime-law/2025/07/09/far-right-groups-co-operating-across-border-as-shared-grievances-override-sectarian-fault-lines/\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.irishtimes.com/crime-law/2025/07/09/far-right-groups-co-operating-across-border-as-shared-grievances-override-sectarian-fault-lines/</a></p>\n", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 25, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"status": 200}, "post_flair_text": "", "archive_id": ""}, {"is_locked": false, "tweet_id": "2048381004209881243", "sticky_comment": 0, "is_video_mp4": false, "type": "link", "uuid": "1ASZaPDx7o", "is_twitter": true, "is_admin": false, "score": 31, "suggested_sort": 0, "post_flair_class": "", "id": 8582968, "raw_content": "", "author": "TRUTH_BE_OUR_DOGMA", "created": 1777223851243, "profile_picture": "", "community": "TheDonald", "ad_tier": 2, "last_comment_author": "Maganifice7", "is_video": false, "video_link": "", "is_new_user": false, "domain": "twitter.com", "is_crosspost": false, "preview": "https://media.scored.co/preview/1ASZaPDx7o.png", "removal_source": "", "link": "https://twitter.com/officer_Lew/status/2048381004209881243", "author_flair_class": "", "is_removed": false, "media": {"resized_resolutions": [], "blurhash": "", "full_resolution": []}, "title": "OL: WATCH\ud83d\udea8: President Trump dropped down to shield Melania and help her to safety as she crawled for cover. Secret Service was urgently pushing him down, yet he put her first \u2014 risking himself in the chaos.\r\n\r\nThat\u2019s leadership. That\u2019s a man who protects his wife. Real men do. (VIDEO)\r\n\r\n", "last_comment_created": 1777225495372, "content": "", "score_down": 0, "author_flair_text": "", "pro_tier": 0, "is_stickied": false, "is_nsfw": false, "is_deleted": false, "is_image": false, "comments": 1, "score_up": 31, "is_edited": false, "is_moderator": false, "awards": 0, "vote_state": 2, "link_metadata": {"twitter": {"quotedTweet": false, "images": false, "linkEmbed": false, "replies": 399, "created": 1777207063000, "id": "2048381004209881243",